Nordic Stocks: DnB NOR, Elisa, Nokia, Novozymes, SSAB Move

-- B y   A d a m   E w i n g
-- 
2011-02-11T16:40:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/elisa-novozymes-oriola-ssab-nokia-nordic-equity-preview.html
The Dow Jones Nordic 30 Index, the
benchmark measure for the region, increased 0.1 percent to
7,586.82 at the 5:30 p.m. close in Stockholm, paring the 0.9
percent loss yesterday and gaining 0.2 percent in the week.  The  OMX Stockholm 30 Index  rose 1.2 percent and the OMX
Copenhagen 20 Index climbed 0.7 percent. The  OMX Helsinki 25
Index  lost 0.7 percent, while Norway’s OBX Index rose 1.5
percent.  The following shares were among the most active in Nordic
markets today. Symbols are in parentheses.  DnB NOR ASA (DNBNOR NO) rose 4.5 percent to 85.30 kroner,
extending yesterday’s increase. Norway’s largest bank was raised
to “buy” from “hold” at Pareto Securities ASA.    Elisa Oyj  (ELI1V FH) climbed 3.9 percent to 16.81 euros,
its second straight advance. The Finnish telephone company
reported fourth-quarter net income of 51.4 million euros ($69.5
million), beating the 46.2 million-euro mean estimate of 14
analysts surveyed by Bloomberg.    Nokia Oyj  (NOK1V FH) plummeted 14 percent to 7 euros, the
biggest drop since July 2009. The world’s biggest maker of
mobile phones announced that it will use Microsoft’s Windows
Phone as its primary software platform -- a sign of the depth of
the challenge in taking on Apple’s iOS and Google’s Android.  Novozymes A/S (NZYMB DC) increased 1.6 percent to 764
kroner, erasing yesterday’s slide. The world’s largest maker of
industrial enzymes said it has started to buy back as much as
400 million kroner ($72.6 million) of “B” shares.    SSAB AB  (SSABA SS) fell 2.4 percent to 103.30 kronor, its
third consecutive slide. The world’s largest supplier of high-
tensile steel reported a fourth-quarter loss before taxes of 176
million kronor, compared with a pretax profit of 348 million
kronor a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
{Adam Ewing} in  Stockholm  at 
